In [59]:
average_premium_by_state = data.groupby('abbrev')['ins_premium'].mean()
plt.bar(average_premium_by_state.index, average_premium_by_state)
plt.xlabel('State Abbreviation')
plt.ylabel('Average Insurance Premium')
plt.title('Bar Chart: Average Insurance Premium by State')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

state NJ pays more Insurance Premium

In [72]:
distracted = data['alcohol'].sum()
non_distracted = data['speeding'].sum()
labels = ['alcohol', 'speeding']
sizes = [distracted, non_distracted]
plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%')
plt.title('Pie Chart: Proportion of alcohol vs. speeding Incidents')
plt.show()

on average the speed and alcohol have same percentages
